        <section class="question-long-text" data-uuid="c62440191f5f466381cb65baead3e24f">
            <object type="text/html" data="../../assets/widgets/long_text_question/index.html" class="widget" data-uuid="b8f13a7d221147fd8534af6f0b3ff73c">
                <param name="configFile" value="../../widget_data/config/b8f13a7d221147fd8534af6f0b3ff73c.json" />
            </object>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="ac4efaa563dd4b20ba620caeebd3769f">Many mill workers were proud of the skills they used, but they did not enjoy their work. Workers often labored 12 hours a day, six days a week. Cotton dust and lint filled the air, causing asthma and an illness known as brown-lung disease. Fast-moving machinery caused injuries and even deaths. Despite the long hours and dangerous working conditions, wages remained low. However, mill work did offer an alternative to farming.<br />
        </p>
